Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.33,0:00:05.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So that happened, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.71,0:00:10.48,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,To think that that's how I'd reunite with Kazuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:18.49,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It seems a lot of different feelings were \Ncolliding in and around this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.27,0:00:21.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What are Minori and the others doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.10,0:00:23.64,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,They're safe, I suppose, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.18,0:02:53.90,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I couldn't make him understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.33,0:02:57.05,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't save the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:03:00.35,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't really useful...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.95,0:03:01.93,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:19.42,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1610,1)}The Skylarks Take Flight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.30,0:03:17.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Skylarks Take Flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.81,0:03:25.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This will take us to Ikoma, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:27.18,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:29.62,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:33.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I do have someplace I'm trying to reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.44,0:03:36.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know where I'll ultimately end up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.22,0:03:38.40,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.77,0:03:42.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to give this to...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.38,0:03:43.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,your brother, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.55,0:03:45.93,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,To Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.93,0:03:47.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.69,0:03:48.67,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.59,0:03:54.08,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:57.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, off I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.87,0:03:59.94,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's such nice weather, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.94,0:04:02.06,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A little too nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:11.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.10,0:04:20.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Would you call me "big sister" one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:23.52,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:25.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I love the sound of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:27.29,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.17,0:04:29.63,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Roe 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.63,0:04:31.59,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:34.75,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet again someday, big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:36.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:43.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Let us meet again, my little brothers and sisters!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.96,0:04:48.31,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,She's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.31,0:04:50.41,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be on my way, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.84,0:04:52.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could stay, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.91,0:04:57.65,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's come to meet me \Nat Sanaru, just up the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.58,0:05:02.77,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It was fun meeting you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:06.03,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we can meet again somewhere, someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:08.00,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:09.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:33.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Was it really all right to let her go like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.24,0:05:34.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.66,0:05:36.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Dariella.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:37.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:45.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.45,0:05:47.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.25,0:05:52.64,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Dariella...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.49,0:05:56.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Her nails were all chewed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.10,0:05:58.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Like she'd bitten them because she was suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:05:59.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.37,0:06:07.41,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,You were always watching her, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.14,0:06:11.85,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm sure it's because you are \Nwho you are that you were able
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:14.55,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,to notice her pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:18.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do you ever bite your nails, Tohya?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.81,0:06:21.69,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... No, now that I think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:23.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Not since I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:24.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:26.59,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What, Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.59,0:06:29.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to say something, say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.34,0:06:34.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Tohya, if something's bothering you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:36.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,just come talk to me, Rundel Haus Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:38.99,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to you? About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.99,0:06:40.88,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,About romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:45.99,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, if I were going to ask someone \Nabout that, it wouldn't be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.99,0:06:47.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.42,0:07:03.17,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Lady Nureha.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.17,0:07:04.67,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,We were worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.51,0:07:31.27,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Can we just leave them like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:36.36,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we could stay a little longer \Nand help with the cleanup.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.36,0:07:41.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, we have the wyvern skins, \Nand we can get the rest in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:44.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We've accomplished our goal, \Nso we shouldn't stay here too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.27,0:07:48.02,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But just leaving doesn't feel right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:50.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.13,0:07:52.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is an important stop on the Red Road.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.44,0:07:54.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be back up in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.26,0:07:56.82,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:07:59.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,the people don't seem that upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.62,0:08:02.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They're used to this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.44,0:08:03.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,For better or worse...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.03,0:08:08.01,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think having more people can hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.01,0:08:09.92,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,If we can help a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:12.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's really okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.79,0:08:15.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Help will come from the neighboring towns.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.19,0:08:17.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.04,0:08:21.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, it's better to not \Nhave any outsiders around...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.07,0:08:25.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to be nice, Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:28.82,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Like, we should leave the People of the \NLand's problems to them or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.09,0:08:31.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, there's no need to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.26,0:08:33.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be just fine on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:37.70,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:38.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:45.67,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it was fate \Nthat brought us together?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.64,0:08:50.02,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What? Does he think he's hitting on us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.02,0:08:52.33,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't he creepy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.33,0:08:55.72,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please become my beautiful bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:58.17,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What burger should we have today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.17,0:09:00.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Or should we have rice balls?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:03.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what we're doing for lunch again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:04.77,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:08.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We also need to decide where we'll \Nget delivery from for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.77,0:09:12.53,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's nothing wrong with eating out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:16.54,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,but since Nyanta left, are we really \Ngetting enough nutrition?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.54,0:09:18.45,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If my skin gets ruined,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.45,0:09:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fans all over the galaxy will go crazy \Nand cause another Big Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:27.92,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If you have time to talk nonsense, \Nwhy don't you make something yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:28.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:32.65,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki and I both gave it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.65,0:09:33.96,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,A try.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.97,0:09:41.47,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,An idol isn't allowed to make anything but sweets!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:43.18,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:48.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.03,0:09:50.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.22,0:09:51.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.95,0:09:54.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.55,0:10:03.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, he must've been jealous of the obvious \Nromance between me and Naotsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:04.91,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't there been a lot more \Npeople like that around?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:11.42,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.10,0:10:16.42,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It reminds me of when we \Nfirst came to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.88,0:10:19.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,At first, there was so much confusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.09,0:10:23.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,and then everyone just sat around, \Nunable to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.56,0:10:26.68,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second, it's only a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:29.94,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Look, there are happy people like that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.55,0:10:36.38,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You're overthinking it. Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.38,0:10:39.09,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You may look like you only think about panties,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.09,0:10:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you're actually really delicate, \Naren't you, Naotsugu?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.85,0:10:43.83,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.36,0:10:46.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you going to ignore that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:48.08,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,She just said pan—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:53.65,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.65,0:10:55.63,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.39,0:10:59.60,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm overthinking it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:01.22,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.77,0:11:07.84,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,But if the same sense of apathy \Nis overcoming Akihabara...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.20,0:11:11.59,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,It might be worse than last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.00,0:11:17.00,Eat Grass,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat Grass
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:23.66,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,This world tried to do something to me that \NI didn't want, regardless of my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.66,0:11:27.04,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm going to do what I want to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.76,0:11:30.47,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,So Londark was talking like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.55,0:11:34.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are more and more adventurers \Nwho can't adapt to this world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.57,0:11:37.05,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and are getting angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:41.04,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But there are people who \Ncan't adapt to this society.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:43.34,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Are we just going to abandon them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.38,0:11:49.03,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And adventurers like that are working with \NPeople of the Land who want to start wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.53,0:11:51.85,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, adventurers even \Nencourage them to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.62,0:11:55.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A war, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.22,0:11:58.39,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think it would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.39,0:12:01.54,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Not between adventurers, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:05.61,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But if the People of the Land \Nget involved, things change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.55,0:12:10.22,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,War has always been a part of their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.77,0:12:13.29,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike us, who were born in peaceful Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.60,0:12:21.01,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And once one starts, will we be able \Nto continue to stay out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:24.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.28,0:12:26.45,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If this were a quest, there'd be no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:30.10,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it were a fight, I can handle monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.54,0:12:31.46,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.89,0:12:33.59,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If a war starts between
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.59,0:12:36.63,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,People of the Land and adventurers, \Nor among adventurers themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.16,0:12:39.90,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,what can the current Round Table do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.92,0:12:43.51,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts not having Crusty here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.06,0:12:48.91,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I hope something comes of what I asked of Isaac...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:12:54.06,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.06,0:12:56.16,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Make them run faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:13:00.40,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They're pathetic, giving up so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.83,0:13:02.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.44,0:13:05.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,People of the Land don't have that much stamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.44,0:13:09.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The villain gave me the most boring jo—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.70,0:13:11.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.84,0:13:13.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Work harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.88,0:13:15.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.46,0:13:17.90,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Isaac!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:24.77,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Isaac...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.27,0:13:29.49,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But why was Sara kidnapped?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.49,0:13:32.60,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Hatred, I guess. The unjustified kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.60,0:13:33.70,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Hatred?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.14,0:13:37.28,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,That Camus guy is no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.28,0:13:39.49,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly, he's a People of the Land merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.49,0:13:42.90,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But he keeps hitting on every girl he sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:46.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,My, he hasn't hit on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.73,0:13:50.79,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, he came after us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.52,0:13:56.48,Default - flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please become my beautiful bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.82,0:14:03.04,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,He was creepy, so we ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.52,0:14:06.49,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess another girl from \Nour guild rejected him before,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.87,0:14:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he's holding a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.11,0:14:10.58,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:22.46,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't Sara acting weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.46,0:14:27.01,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She looks more like she's been \Nseduced than kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:27.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.58,0:14:31.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, he's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.38,0:14:32.30,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Kurinon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.88,0:14:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard! What have you done to Sara?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:40.56,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please become my beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:43.02,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Heck, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.65,0:14:45.19,Green HUD,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Camus /Traveling Merchant
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.65,0:14:45.19,Sara,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sara /Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.65,0:14:45.19,HUD Big,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HF1DAC6&\fs18\an6}Kurinon /Priest, Lv. 91
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:46.96,Monsters,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Genius of Marriage\NCamaysar /Genius, Lv. 83\NRank /Party
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:49.21,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The genius...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.21,0:14:50.20,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,...of marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.75,0:14:51.50,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.50,0:14:52.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sara!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.37,0:14:55.37,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, she's just knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:15:00.04,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Fate must have brought us together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:04.26,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You want to get hit again, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.27,0:15:14.93,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please become my beautiful bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.92,0:15:20.06,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.62,0:15:22.96,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,No way! Not Kurinon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.96,0:15:24.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.54,0:15:26.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he's using some kind of strange skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.27,0:15:29.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Souji!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.23,0:15:30.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sou!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.95,0:15:33.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose these weirdos
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.73,0:15:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are showing up now because the \Ndefensive barrier is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.71,0:15:41.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you deceive these girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:47.42,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please become my beautiful bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.97,0:15:56.39,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you say that to Sou?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my! You're into that sort of thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.18,0:16:02.56,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot to carry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.22,0:16:06.79,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,In times like these, I wish we had a magic bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.79,0:16:09.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is all stuff to make a magic bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.61,0:16:13.32,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I think you did great, Tohya.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.52,0:16:16.95,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,When you were talking with that knight...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.47,0:16:20.55,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is it that important
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.55,0:16:22.50,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,whether you can die or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.09,0:16:26.81,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever died?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.39,0:16:30.55,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ever die in the old world?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.50,0:16:34.05,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You told him exactly how you felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.51,0:16:36.93,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't make him understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.90,0:16:40.06,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.55,0:16:43.78,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he doesn't understand yet, \Nhe won't forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:47.24,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I think there's meaning in the fact \Nthat you were able to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.58,0:16:50.80,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's so amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.80,0:16:54.57,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Minori, Tohya, Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.92,0:16:58.16,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Even Rudy, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:01.19,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone seems like they're \Nreally doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.19,0:17:03.09,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,So are you, Serara.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.09,0:17:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.35,0:17:10.34,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,On this journey, I realized that \NI have a long way to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.21,0:17:14.09,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I understood that, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:20.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to have to walk home...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:22.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You okay, Miss Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.76,0:17:25.32,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.32,0:17:27.98,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't as far as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:36.86,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we ask the people around here if \Nthey need any of the stuff we don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:40.37,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It might be better than throwing it away...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.37,0:17:44.71,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.71,0:17:46.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they would protect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.99,0:17:49.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But they were useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:51.81,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Some heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.81,0:17:53.88,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, they're just adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:56.15,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,They don't care about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.93,0:17:59.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, Isuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.39,0:18:00.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't talking about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:02.06,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.62,0:18:05.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They're talking about those knights, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.09,0:18:07.09,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.30,0:18:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand why you wanted to get \Nus out of here as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.63,0:18:21.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I think a lot of people's lives were saved \Nbecause the knights were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:27.57,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But there are some people who feel betrayed \Nbecause they got their hopes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.43,0:18:31.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we're also adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:34.18,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We might be blamed for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:36.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.36,0:18:41.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something you need to apologize for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.28,0:18:46.38,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm really glad we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.38,0:18:51.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,All the things that were bothering \Nme seem so small now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.12,0:18:55.54,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So I wanted to do something for this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.07,0:18:58.45,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to leave something for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.09,0:19:01.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You gave them a forty-three..
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:05.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A new song that never existed in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.17,0:19:10.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That song... It's hope! Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.97,0:19:12.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Rudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.90,0:19:16.59,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But if it doesn't remain here, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.49,0:19:32.55,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Our journey's over, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.55,0:19:33.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.70,0:19:39.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.61,0:19:41.49,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A song?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:42.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A song?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.69,0:19:44.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're right! That song!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.97,0:19:58.71,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:01.29,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.55,0:20:06.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You made a new song.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.76,0:20:12.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And now, that song will become \Na new hope for those kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.53,0:20:30.20,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're singing Isuzu's song over there, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.03,0:20:34.58,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,This is as far as we were able to come, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:37.98,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but this song...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.70,0:20:40.75,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It'll go farther west.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.75,0:20:44.43,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It will spread out around the whole world!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.29,0:20:51.47,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,And it'll give everyone the \Nmost important thing: hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.53,0:21:09.69,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A griffon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.03,0:21:14.39,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.52,0:21:17.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.56,0:21:18.71,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.31,0:21:28.72,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It'd been so long since we'd seen Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.34,0:21:34.18,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And the city and everyone's smiles \Nseemed so bright, so hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:39.01,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I felt my whole body relaxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.04,0:21:43.74,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,All the tension just disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.43,0:21:48.94,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.83,0:21:59.77,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... We've always been protected \Nhere, by these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.70,0:22:04.46,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I remembered that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.10,0:22:14.98,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Afterward, everyone else and I fell asleep, \Nthough we don't remember when.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.51,0:22:20.03,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But I remember Roe 2 appeared in my dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.10,0:22:24.69,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Even in my dream, she was a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.31,0:24:12.38,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Unknown monsters, the Geniuses, \Nsneak into Akihabara to cause chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.38,0:24:14.30,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.30,0:24:18.23,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The letter from Roe 2 holds \Nthe key to that mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.23,0:24:21.76,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,There is still something in this world that \NShiroe and the others know nothing of.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.76,0:24:24.77,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land, the adventurers, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.77,0:24:26.43,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.77,0:24:30.94,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Stranger
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.43,0:24:28.26,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,I have friends to run with me.
